canonical:
  title: 賀正牋
  author: 李崇仁
  language: lzh
  text: 道長三陽布大和而育物位尊貳極陳縟禮以盈庭喜氣交騰頌聲旁達恭惟性敦忠孝德著溫文主器承祧式端天下之本尊師重傅克遵聖人之謨新正甫回景命益固伏念猥將庸質權襲弊封載賡輝潤之謌恒貢康寧之祝
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賀正牋
  author: 李崇仁
  language: lzh
  text: 道長三陽。布大和而育物。位尊貳極。陳縟禮以盈庭。喜氣交騰。頌聲旁達。恭惟性敦忠孝。德著溫文。主器承祧。式端天下之本。尊師重傅。克遵聖人之謨。新正甫回。景命益固。伏念猥將庸質。權襲弊封。載賡輝潤之謌。恒貢康寧之祝。
korean:
  title: 하정전
  author: 이숭인
  language: kor
  text: 삼양(三陽)과 함께 도(道)가 길어지는 때 대화(大和)를 펴서 만물을 기르시고, 이극(貳極)에 위(位)가 높으사 화려한 예식에 하례 올리는 반열이 뜰에 가득하오니, 기쁜 기운이 솟아오르고 찬송하는 소리가 사방에 들끓나이다. 공손히 생각하옵건대, 성품은 충효에 돈독하시고 덕은 온문(溫文)으로 드러나사, 종묘와 황통(皇統)을 이으실 귀한 자격으로 천하의 근본이 되셨고, 사부를 존중하시어 성인의 예(禮)를 잘 따르시오니, 신정(新正)이 갓 돌아오자 큰 명(命)이 더욱 굳으시리이다. 엎드려 생각하옵건대, 외람되게 용렬한 자질로 덕분에 폐봉(弊封)을 승습(承襲)하여 휘윤(輝潤)의 노래를 이어 부르며 항상 강녕(康寧)의 축원을 바치옵나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0350_010_0460&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: A Missive of New Year's Congratulations
  author: Lee Sung-in
  language: eng
  text: 'With the Three Yangs comes the lengthening of the Way, spreading Great Harmony to nurture all things. Elevated in rank at the Second Pole, ceremonies magnificent fill the courtyard with reverent gatherings, as joy ascends and songs of praise echo through all directions. I humbly contemplate: Your nature is rooted in loyalty and filial piety, your virtue radiant in gentleness and grace. In the honor of continuing the ancestral temple and imperial line, you have become the foundation of all under Heaven. Revering teachers and exemplars, you follow faithfully the teachings of the sages. As the new year turns, your mandate grows ever stronger. With utmost respect, I offer these humble words: Though my talents are meager and unworthy, I am privileged to inherit this modest station and thus add my voice to the songs of brightness, ever presenting wishes for your peace and prosperity.'
  footnotes:
    - The 'Three Yangs' (三陽) refers to the auspicious beginning of the new year in traditional Chinese cosmology, where yang energy is ascendant.
    - The 'Second Pole' (貳極) is a poetic reference to the position of a high-ranking official or heir, positioned beneath the throne.
    - This work is a formal congratulatory missive (箋) presented to a dignitary at New Year, a common literary form in classical East Asian court literature.
